About

The Project

In this project, I explore the ratings of professors on campuses across America. All the code for data collection and analysis can be found on my academic github. In this project, I look to determine if the distribution of ratings differs from college to college. I also look to see if the distribution of ratings correlates at all with the median salary of graduates of the college.

The Data

The data that I am working with concern the ratings of professors across different colleges, and the median salaries of graduates of those colleges.

Rating Data

I wrote a script in python, that I use to collect professor rating data from Rate My Professor. Some thought should be put in to whether the ratings are truly representative of the general student opinion of these teachers and readers should just keep in mind that it represents ratings as reported in this specific context. Salary Data
